                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a salesman, in Giltspur-street: On Saturday, between one and two, I saw one of the prisoners, he in the brown coat, unpin the waistcoat; the other immediately took it, and ran away with it; I pursued him, and took him at the second Hospital gate; I immediately carried him to the Compter; this is the waistcoat, (producing it); it has my mark upon it; I am sure he is the same man; I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>William Peat's defence. I had not been with my brother the space of three hours, when I was taken, they detained me, and said I was with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17960217-64-person659">
                  Robert
                   Peat
               <interp inst="t17960217-64-person659" type="surname" value="Peat"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17960217-64-person659" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17960217-64-person659" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's defence. I never had the waistcoat in my hand; going through Giltspur-street, I heard a cry of stop thief, and they said I had the waistcoat.(The prisoner Robert called 
               <persName id="t17960217-64-person660">
                  William
                   Hurst
               <interp inst="t17960217-64-person660" type="surname" value="Hurst"></interp>
